<module>
    <h>sinn</h>
    <p><g>sinn</g>
        <en>we, us</en> is the first person plural <a href="?xx=nouns/personal_pronouns">personal
            pronoun</a>.</p>

    <section>
        <h>verbs</h>
        <section id="verbs-sbj">
            <h>subject</h>
            <!--<p><g>sinn</g> can be used as the subject of a verb.</p>-->
            <p>Examples with the predicative verb <g href="?gd=bi">bi</g>
                <en>be</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha sinn trang.</gd>
                        <tr>We are busy.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha sinn trang ag obair.</gd>
                        <tr>We ae busy working.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 9</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>A bheil sibh trang? Chan eil. Chan eil sinn trang an diugh.</gd>
                        <tr>Are you busy? No, we are not busy today.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Cha robh sinn a’ cluich anns an taigh.</gd>
                        <tr>We were not playing in the house.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 21 [230]</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
            <p>Examples with other verbs – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd><a href="?gd=faic">Chunnaic</a> sinn iolair mhór an diugh.</gd>
                        <tr>We saw a big eagle today..</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 9 [226]</ref>
                    </li>
                <li>
                    <gd>Chunnaic sinn iolair mhór an diugh.</gd>
                    <tr>We saw a big eagle today.</tr>
                    <ref text="617">td. 9 [226]</ref>
                </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>




